# Updating your scratchpad

Updating your existing VoodooPad 4 scratchpad to work with VoodooPad 5 is very easy:

1. Open your existing VoodooPad 4 scratchpad in VoodooPad 5. When it asks if you want to back it up before converting it, choose to do so (better safe than sorry).
2. Create a new page and name it "VPJSPrefixScript" and replace the default contents with this template's VPJSPrefixScript
3. Create a new page and name it "VPPageEventScript" and replace the default contents with this template's VPPageEventScript
4. Create a new page and name it "VPWebExportScript" and replace the default contents with this template's VPWebExportScript

A console window may open when you create VPPageEventScript (because the default page event script that VoodooPad creates outputs things to the console). You can close this window.

You can also delete the pages "Script_Autogenerate" and "Script_WebProcess" from your original scratchpad if you wish. Otherwise, you should be ready to use your scratchpad with VoodooPad 5!
